I understand that she could have been frustrated with people moving stickers on items but it was clear that a big part of the issue was that they were not marking their items accurately seeing as she said my items were not included in the sale yet many of the records had stickers and when I tried to inform her of this she was beyond rude. I know customer service is frustrating but she had no reason to speak to anyone the way that she spoke to me today. Drew was GREAT. I had recently been given a BN gift card and I didn't really have an idea of what to get since I haven't been an avid reader for years. I absentmindedly asked for a book I've heard good things about. Drew showed me where it was, said he loved it and would be happy to give similar recommendations. I told him no thanks at first but after a while of failing to find anything that piqued my interest, I searched for him again and asked for his opinions. He proceeded to give a good 10 minute in depth talk about horror books he loves and what he thinks might appeal to me; I grabbed a particularly interesting sounding book he recommended  and he was kind enough to reduce it 50% as a Christmas gift. It was nice to see someone talk so passionately, especially when it's something related to their field of work. Days later and I cannot put these books down (Drew knows his stuff)
